# Code Quality Rules

This project follows strict code quality standards. Always adhere to these rules when making changes.

## Before Committing

### 1. Run Tests

Always run the test suite before committing any changes:

```bash
flutter test
```

All tests must pass before committing. If any test fails:
- Fix the failing tests
- Ensure your changes don't break existing functionality
- Add new tests for new functionality

### 2. Run Linter

Always run the linter and fix any issues before committing:

```bash
# Check code formatting
dart format --set-exit-if-changed --line-length 80 lib test

# Run static analysis
flutter analyze
```

If formatting issues are found, fix them with:
```bash
dart format --line-length 80 lib test
```

All linting rules must pass with zero warnings or errors.

### 3. Pre-Commit Checklist

Before every commit, verify:
- [ ] All tests pass (`flutter test`)
- [ ] Code is properly formatted (`dart format --set-exit-if-changed --line-length 80 lib test`)
- [ ] Static analysis passes (`flutter analyze`)
- [ ] No new warnings or errors introduced

## After Pushing

### Wait for CI to Complete

Always wait for the CI pipeline to finish successfully before considering a task complete:

1. Push your changes to the remote branch
2. Monitor the GitHub Actions workflow status
3. If CI fails:
   - Review the failure logs
   - Fix the issues locally
   - Run tests and linter again
   - Push the fixes
4. Only mark the task as complete when CI passes

The CI pipeline runs:
- Code formatting check
- Static analysis (181 linting rules)
- Full test suite

## Summary

**Never commit without:**
1. Running `flutter test` - all tests must pass
2. Running `dart format --line-length 80 lib test` - code must be formatted
3. Running `flutter analyze` - no analysis issues

**Never finish a task without:**
- Waiting for CI to complete successfully on GitHub
